</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BE918666EE96B703F4ECB7B8425FF1EB" pageId="8" pageNumber="19" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="73EB5808ED3B7055036CFB83725E5398" pageId="8" pageNumber="19">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="68B0C25F8EED16B01DD9A53F95D618F8" pageId="8" pageNumber="19">
Some authors (e.g 
<bibRefCitation id="A438898851EEBB4F59F31C8F2B9E4F1F" author="Subba Rao, NV" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Survey of India, Calcutta" pageId="19" pageNumber="30" refId="B58" refString="Subba Rao, NV, 1989. Handbook Freshwater Molluscs of India. Zoological Survey of India, Calcutta, 289 pp." title="Handbook Freshwater Molluscs of India." year="1989">Subba Rao 1989</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="57C68259657F79A2888092E446E1CDFF" author="Nesemann, H" journalOrPublisher="Malacologia" pageId="19" pageNumber="30" refId="B45" refString="Nesemann, H, Sharma, S, Sharma, G, Khanal, SN, Pradhan, B, Shah, DN, Tachamo, RD, 2007. Aquatic invertebrates of the Ganga River System. Mollusca, Annelida, Crustacea (in part), 1, 263 pp." title="Aquatic invertebrates of the Ganga River System. Mollusca, Annelida, Crustacea (in part), 1, 263 pp." year="2007">Nesemann et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
) mention 
<taxonomicName id="7368D19F83635292772A5EF4BA046F03" authorityName="Tryon" authorityYear="1865" class="Gastropoda" family="Bithyniidae" genus="Gabbia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="8" pageNumber="19" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="ED63FEA03BBD3FAAE12A42E3306D8117" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="19">Gabbia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a genus. However, it seems not possible to distinguish the genera of the 
<taxonomicName id="2F198B460646FA2A365C6C048A94BA2E" class="Gastropoda" family="Bithyniidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="8" pageNumber="19" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Bithyniidae</taxonomicName>
by the shape of opercula (
<bibRefCitation id="3D031004FF75B70BC8908100E477221A" author="Mandahl-Barth, G" journalOrPublisher="Revue de zoologie et de botanique africaines" pageId="19" pageNumber="30" pagination="129 - 159" refId="B34" refString="Mandahl-Barth, G, 1968. Revision of the African Bithyniidae (Gastropoda Prosobranchia). Revue de zoologie et de botanique africaines 78 (1-2): 129 - 159" title="Revision of the African Bithyniidae (Gastropoda Prosobranchia)." volume="78" year="1968">Mandahl-Barth 1968</bibRefCitation>
) and/or by shell forms, because these characters are found to be variable. On the other hand, the examined material of the family of 
<taxonomicName id="8A1EE22B1A4C48922B1EC697A91B41F9" class="Gastropoda" family="Bithyniidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="8" pageNumber="19" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Bithyniidae</taxonomicName>
can be easily separated by the characteristics of penis morphology (having a penial appendix: 
<taxonomicName id="9968028B974A173506D40AE096F15ABE" class="Gastropoda" family="Bithyniidae" genus="Bithynia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="8" pageNumber="19" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1CD4493871FD90F8ED1F9E4BA7B9E695" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="19">Bithynia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Leach 1818; or lacking a penial appendix: 
<taxonomicName id="7245FAB4C5A9D4597B833F3E606D9457" authorityName="Gloer &amp; Pesic" authorityYear="2006" class="Gastropoda" family="Bithyniidae" genus="Pseudobithynia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="8" pageNumber="19" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="296F4E52D8747F78FB054FA6738376B5" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="19">Pseudobithynia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="DF450206A5D2B55A59DDE976AEDE130C" originalValue="Glöer">Gloeer</normalizedToken>
&amp; 
<normalizedToken id="42DC50B2973EAB1D3738953ABBCAD5FB" originalValue="Pešić">Pesic</normalizedToken>
2006). In our study, we tentatively use the name 
<taxonomicName id="347E9438C2984672A6DDCD9A28BDDB2B" authorityName="Tryon" authorityYear="1865" class="Gastropoda" family="Bithyniidae" genus="Gabbia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="8" pageNumber="19" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="12BF868D3265E41319FD5DC78F2346F8" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="19">Gabbia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a subgenus for small 
<taxonomicName id="338ABEE1168EA22CB8980EC5B0347032" class="Gastropoda" family="Bithyniidae" genus="Bithynia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="8" pageNumber="19" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1996AC3D6880D938BFE1F90CAB372FF9" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="19">Bithynia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species with a globular shell, originating from India.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
